  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PDP Pre-inception</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Save the Children have been identified by DFID as the preferred supplier for the delivery of the Basic Service Component of the Peace and Development Programme (PDP-BS). During the final stages of the procurement process it was agreed between Save the Children and DFID that the formal programme launch and initial partner workshops, as well as a targeted number of time-critical inception phase activities should commence in the week of the 29th October 2012. This approach was agreed to ensure that momentum around the start-up, and the buy-in and commitment of the Somali Regional Government could be harnessed to its maximum in the initial and critical phases of project start-up. This submission to DFID-Ethiopia (DFID-E) reflects the costs that have been incurred by Save the Children in the period from the 29th October 2012 up to the anticipated date of contracting.</narrative>
  </description>
